The highlighter seems to not work after an arrow function is annotated with an optional return type. In the attached screenshot, you can see that const/let/return in the same scope as the arrow function are highlighted incorrectly.

- VSCode Version:  Version 1.10.2
- OS Version: Ubuntu 16.10

Steps to reproduce:
```js
/* @flow */
(function () {
    const b = (): ?Number => {
        const c = 1;
        return c;
    };
    const a = 1;
    let inner = b;
    return function () { return b; };
})();

```

![screenshot from 2017-03-16 12-38-32](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/115951/24021720/efda0ddc-0a67-11e7-9e1a-670e1a095a56.png)
